BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE-URLS:{"Ucdavis Library": "https://events.library.ucdavis.edu/event/ai-literacy-logic-spring-2026"}
X-SOURCE-ID:ucdavis_library
SUMMARY:AI Literacy & Logic: 1-day intensive course
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260410T160000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260410T233000
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_52340792785132
DESCRIPTION:A 198 course for College of Letters & Science majors.\n\nThe l
 andscape of the academic and professional world is shifting. Whether you a
 re an aspiring historian\, a budding chemist\, or a future sociologist\, A
 I is no longer a "tech" skill—it’s a foundational literacy.\n\nDevelop
 ed through a collaboration between the UC Davis College of Letters & Scien
 ce and DataLab\, this 1-unit intensive course is designed to unveil Artifi
 cial Intelligence. We’ve stripped away the dense math and complex coding
  to give you a conceptual\, high-level understanding of how artificial int
 elligence systems work\, why they matter\, and how to make them work for y
 ou.\n\nWhy Enroll?\n\nIn a single day\, you will move from being a passive
  AI user to a critical\, strategic collaborator. This training is specific
 ally curated for L&S students to ensure you graduate with the competitive 
 edge needed for the rapidly evolving\, AI-driven workplace.\n\nNo technica
 l background? No problem. This course has no prerequisites. It is designed
  for thinkers\, writers\, and researchers across all liberal arts and scie
 nce disciplines.\n\nThe curriculum is divided into four deep-dive modules:
 \n\nHow AI Thinks\nUnderstand the "brain" of the machine. We’ll explore 
 the theories of language and cognition that allow Large Language Models (L
 LMs) to function\, and provide a framework for evaluating their potential 
 and limits.\n\nHow to Use AI Responsibly\nAI isn't a magic wand—it’s a
  tool with a history and consequences. We discuss the environmental and so
 cietal impacts\, how to ensure the veracity of AI results\, and why reprod
 ucibility is the cornerstone of ethical tech.\n\nHow to Talk with AI\nMast
 er the art and science of prompt engineering. Learn what happens behind th
 e scenes when you send a prompt. Develop sophisticated strategies to get t
 he exact results you need.\n\nModule 4: How AI Talks with You\nA look at t
 he future of AI implementation. From simple chatbots to complex autonomous
  "Agents\," learn how AI is being embedded into systems and how to evaluat
 e its activity.\n\nBy the end of this one-day course\, you will be able to
 :\n\nDefine "AI" and distinguish it from traditional statistics and data s
 cience.\n\nIdentify whether a real-world problem is suitable for an AI sol
 ution.\n\nDevelop advanced prompting strategies that produce reliable\, us
 eful results.\n\nCritically interrogate your own engagement with AI and it
 s impact on our society and environment.\n\n \n\nRegister Now\n\nThis inte
 nsive\, one-day course will be offered five times during the Spring Quarte
 r 2026. You only need to register for one date.\n\nTime: 9:00 AM – 4:30 
 PM (with a break for lunch)\n\nCredits: 1 Unit\n\nCRN: TBA\n\nEligibility:
  Open to all students with a major in the College of Letters & Science.\n\
 nPriority: Registration priority is given to Seniors (4th years) and stude
 nts graduating in Spring or Summer 2026. Other students in the College are
  encouraged to enroll and will be admitted as space permits.
URL:https://events.library.ucdavis.edu/event/ai-literacy-logic-spring-2026
X-SOURCE:UC Davis Library
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE-URLS:{"Davis Downtown": "https://davisdowntown.com/event/2nd-friday-artabout/2026-04-10/"}
X-SOURCE-ID:davis_downtown
SUMMARY:2nd Friday ArtAbout – Monthly Downtown Davis Art Walk & Receptio
 ns (Free!)
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260410T170000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260410T210000
UID:10000170-1775840400-1775854800@davisdowntown.com
DESCRIPTION:Join Davis’s beloved 2nd Friday ArtAbout – a free monthly 
 self-guided artwalk coordinated by the Pence Gallery! Every second Friday\
 , stroll downtown Davis to discover fresh exhibits\, opening receptions\, 
 live music\, hands-on activities\, and direct chats with local and regiona
 l artists at 10+ galleries\, co-ops\, and businesses. \nSupport our vibran
 t arts scene\, uncover unique talent and styles\, and soak up the lively e
 nergy – ideal for friends\, families\, dates\, or solo adventures. Many 
 venues offer complimentary refreshments like wine and snacks. \nFree – n
 o tickets required! \n\nRuns approximately 5:00–9:00 PM (venue reception
 s vary—check the monthly guide for specifics).\nGrab the printed guide (
 with map & details) the week of at the Pence Gallery or participating spot
 s\, or download it at pencegallery.org/events/artabout/.\n\nInterested in 
 hosting as a venue\, artist\, or business? Visit https://pencegallery.org/
 events/artabout/ to fill out the corresponding forms. Please submit event
 s 3 weeks in advance via the form on the site to be included in the guide 
 and promotions. \nStay in the loop: facebook.com/davisartabout \nCome cele
 brate local creativity downtown – see you on the next second Friday! 
 🎨✨
URL:https://davisdowntown.com/event/2nd-friday-artabout/2026-04-10/
X-SOURCE:Davis Downtown
END:VEVENT
